From 0e300b9f6846426e6dcef6106a1f4d1f97deb1bb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: psyclyx <me@psyclyx.xyz>
Date: Thu, 2 Apr 2026 02:51:09 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] feat: add Wayland compositor to SurfaceFlinger

Embed a Wayland compositor inside SurfaceFlinger that allows native
Wayland clients to render into SF layers. Implements:

- wl_compositor + wl_surface: create SF layers from Wayland clients
- zwp_linux_dmabuf_v1: import DMA-BUF backed buffers
- wl_shm: shared memory buffer path with CPU copy
- xdg_wm_base + xdg_surface + xdg_toplevel: XDG shell protocol
- wl_output: display geometry reporting
- wl_seat: input device stubs (pointer/keyboard)
- VSYNC-aligned wl_callback.done frame callbacks
- Post-composite wl_buffer.release signaling

The compositor listens on /data/wayland/wayland-0 and integrates
with SF's Looper for event dispatch. Each wl_surface maps to a
BufferState SF Layer.

Ported from lineage-22.1 development tree to lineage-23.2.

Change-Id: I51816759e0ecd71f06443e67c8a660bce2e29c7f
